CFL-012: Guard CIccCLUT::InterpND against NULL CIccApplyCLUT (CWE-476)

CIccXformNDLut::Apply() calls InterpND(Pixel, Pixel, pNDApply->m_pApply)
at two sites without checking if m_pApply is NULL. When BPC (Black Point
Compensation) creates a temporary CIccCmm during Begin() and calls Apply()
recursively, the NDLut apply object may have a NULL CIccApplyCLUT pointer.

Trigger: 11-channel MCHBData profile processed through iccApplyProfiles
with BPC enabled. CIccApplyBPC::pixelXfm() -> CIccCmm::Apply() ->
CIccXformNDLut::Apply() -> CIccCLUT::InterpND(pApply=NULL) -> SEGV.

Confirmed 3/3 reproducible against upstream iccApplyProfiles (unpatched).

Bug: IccProfLib/IccCmm.cpp lines 6579-6580 and 6609-6610
CWE-476 (NULL Pointer Dereference)

--- a/IccProfLib/IccCmm.cpp
+++ b/IccProfLib/IccCmm.cpp
@@ -6576,8 +6576,13 @@
       default:
         {
           CIccApplyNDLutXform* pNDApply = (CIccApplyNDLutXform*)pApply;
-          m_pTag->m_CLUT->InterpND(Pixel, Pixel, pNDApply->m_pApply);
-          break;
+          if (pNDApply && pNDApply->m_pApply) {
+            m_pTag->m_CLUT->InterpND(Pixel, Pixel, pNDApply->m_pApply);
+          } else {
+            // CFL-012: NULL ApplyCLUT — zero output to prevent use of uninitialized data
+            memset(DstPixel, 0, m_pTag->m_nOutput * sizeof(icFloatNumber));
+          }
+          break; 
         }
       }
     }
@@ -6606,8 +6611,13 @@
       default:
       {
         CIccApplyNDLutXform* pNDApply = (CIccApplyNDLutXform*)pApply;
-        m_pTag->m_CLUT->InterpND(Pixel, Pixel, pNDApply->m_pApply);
-        break;
+        if (pNDApply && pNDApply->m_pApply) {
+          m_pTag->m_CLUT->InterpND(Pixel, Pixel, pNDApply->m_pApply);
+        } else {
+          // CFL-012: NULL ApplyCLUT — zero output to prevent use of uninitialized data
+          memset(DstPixel, 0, m_pTag->m_nOutput * sizeof(icFloatNumber));
+        }
+        break;
       }
       break;
       }
